cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

The paper presents an implementation of a saliency model for predicting where humans would look in a given image. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves image analysis and prediction. The implementation also supports training and testing, which suggests machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE) may be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for further research in visual attention modeling, which could involve information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
